message:
Hi Steven,

Thank you very much for the link. But unfortunately I can't use .NET 4.6. I tried to use it with .Net 4.5.1, but had no success.  
What I figured out is that I can use my normal relay command which takes a parameter and do something like this:

public ICommand StoreSelectedCommand  
{  
get   
{  
 if (this._storeSelectedCommand == null)  
{  
 this._storeSelectedCommand = new RelayCommand<unit>(  
async (commandParameter) =>{ await Task.Run(() => StoreSelectedAsync(commandParameter)); }  
);  
 }  
 return this._storeSelectedCommand;  
 }  
}

My exception handling is done in the called procedure.

Thanks again to Michigan, where I spent three wonderful years.
